               <head>Gulshan-i tauhid</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of Gulshan-i tawḥīd by Mawlavī Ibrāhīm ibn Khudāʾī Dadah al-Rūmī Būrsavī</summary>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85129656 http://lccn.loc.gov/n81058129 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85084471" n="1" xml:id="Uk_IO_Islamic_4394-item1">
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" type="supplied" key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164656911.0x000001 viaf_24509051">Mawlavī Ibrāhīm ibn Khudāʾī Dadah al-Rūmī Būrsavī</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" type="supplied" key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164656911.0x000001 viaf_24509051">مولوى ابراهيم ابن خدائى دده الرّومى بورسوى</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_10185">Gulshan-i tawḥīd</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_10185">گلشن توحيد</title>
                     <note>
                        <p>Mystical poem in mukhammas form based on selected verses from Rumi Balkhi's <title>Mas̲navī-yi maʿnavī</title>, with further verses added in the same metre, composed in 940/1533-4
                        </p>
                        <p>The work is organised into 6 volumes or jild, like its model</p>
                        <p>Every sixth line, or first line of every pentad or mukhammas, is written in red</p>
                        <p>Not dated</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per">Persian</textLang>
                     <note />
                  </msItem>
